storyInfo: Bibeak takes the first step towards a new life, but some things don't go as planned.

attributes.content: Orchid... I, I'm still nervous.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Happens to everyone on their first mission. Don't worry, I'm here for you.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Trust the time you've spent in the training room. You could give anyone a run for their money with your sword.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Gloompincers are really fierce, aren't they? If the villagers couldn't chase them away, I...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I won't pretend that they're not dangerous, but I guarantee you that they're not as scary as Instructor Dur-nar's sword, or Instructor Dobermann's whip.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: They approved you for this mission because they believe you have the skills.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: This is just the first step. It took you a long time to make up your mind, didn't it?
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Yeah...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: So this is how it feels to sit in this car.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: When operators from the office came to find us, I was thinking maybe I should wait for the next chance. But I felt like this was a step that I had to take, and so I raised my hand.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I haven't seen Instructor Dobermann smile like that for ages. I'll get this mission done.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I want to use this sword to help protect more people.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: That's more like it.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Tell me about your first mission! I want to know how you felt.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Well, that was a long time ago. I was leading the squad...
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Anyway, I almost quit after that mission.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: But they started listening... I guess.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: So that's what they were like back then...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Excuse me...
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Are you girls from Rhodes Island?
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Yes, we are.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Why don't you explain our mission to them?
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Hello, we're here from Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: We'll set up defenses outside the village, and instruct you guys on how to set them up afterwards.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: The defenses are equipped with warning systems, giving you a chance to prepare the next time there's a gloompincer attack, and reducing the damage to the village.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: We'll also help you defeat them if they attack.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Alright. Er... I have another question.
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Go ahead.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Well, you talk so slowly, and your sword is so thin. Why did Rhodes Island send someone like you?
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Can you really beat the gloompincers?
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Excuse me? Please—
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Trust me, I can.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Ah... well, I'm just speaking my mind here, but...
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: I figured a lady like you would be more comfortable reading a book and having tea, not doing rough stuff like this. Don't want you to get hurt, you know.
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: We're really grateful you came to help, though.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Come in, we have tea and snacks if you like. We made them ourselves.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Thank you.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: The tea was great, thank you.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: It was from last year's harvest. The gloompincers made a mess of the tea fields this year, and we couldn't plant much in the fields we have left.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Life's hard.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Have you ever thought about leaving this place and doing something else?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Where would we go? It's not that easy.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Even the factories are looking for people who've been to school. Folks like us, we just stick to our fields and see what our kids and grandkids can do.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: I'm sorry...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Oh, it's nothing. I see you girls are pretty well-dressed. Is this some kinda upper-class hobby, coming out here to train?
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Know anyone who's hiring and pays a steady wage? We'd love to know.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Don't think we'll last more than a few more years, the way things are headed.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: We're not exactly upper-class, just employees of our company.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: But we could talk afterwards about your situation. We might be able to help somehow.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Oh, thank you so much.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Hey! We spotted some gloompincers! Grab your weapons!
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Go, go!
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Our village can't take much more of this! Please, help us chase them away!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: We'd really appreciate it!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Stay on high ground! We've got it covered down here!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Don't worry, we've fought them plenty of times ourselves!
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: We'll guard this side, help lighten the load on you guys!
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Alright! Just hold these barricades. Watch out for Arts from above!
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: You guys can use Arts?
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Wow! I hear good casters can blow up a whole building by themselves! This'll be a piece of cake with you guys around!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Don't get too excited. I'm not that powerful.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Just being able to use Arts is amazing enough!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Look out! Wright, Patty, activate the shield's circuit!
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Got it!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A&B

attributes.content: Wow, that's so cool!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: You're really letting us keep this?
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: This way, you won't need to call us in every time something happens, and we get to save some time and effort.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: It's a win-win!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: Wow, you guys are so nice!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Ah!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Look out, Orchid! They're coming!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Did you get hurt?
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Just a scratch on the shoulder. I can deal with it.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Bibeak tears off a piece of her outfit to wrap up the wound, revealing her neck.
Huh...?
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: (Hey, that thing on her neck... is that Originium?)
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: (What?)
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: (Shit!)
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Hey, you, you're Infected?!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Yeah! You've got rocks growing out of you!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: G-Get away from us!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: What did you say?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: You're Infected, right?
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Damn, we even had tea together! Did I—
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Damn you, gloompincers, why do you keep coming for us?! Go get those damned Infected, would you?!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: A villager throws some food in the direction of the squad.
The gloompincers follow the trail of the scent.
Eat them!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: I-I'd rather have the gloompincers eat everything I own than catch Oripathy!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: How did you even get here?!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: You asked—
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: We never asked for any Infected!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: But we're helping you!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: You even invited us to your house!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: That's because we didn't know you were Infected!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: You lied to us! How is anyone supposed to tell when you hide your Originium under your clothes like that!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: What did you say?!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: Get out! Get out!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Chase them out, gloompincers!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: What the heck are you babbling about? Oripathy doesn't spread through everyday contact!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: I'm not Infected, but I've worked with them for years, and I'm completely fine!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: You're not Infected? Then you're a nutjob!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Bill got the illness from who knows where, and he couldn't find a job after rocks started growing out of him, not even at the bottom of the mines!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Even after he died, he... our village is like this now because of the Infected!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: How dare you stroll in like you own the place! Are you trying to kill us all?
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Are you here to help us or kill us?!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Get out! All of you! We don't need your help!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: You're the squad leader, Orchid. Your call.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator B

attributes.content: Personally, I don't see a need to stay here and take this abuse and the gloompincers.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator B

attributes.content: Let's finish this one off and leave, Bibeak. They've made their choice, and we have no obligation to stay.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: I'll be coming down now. Go around the barricades, and we'll meet by the car!
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Why should we have to be chased out like this...?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: We did nothing wrong!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: We came to—
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Another piece of food flies towards Bibeak and lands by her feet. Nearby gloompincers detect the scent and converge upon her.
Orchid repels them with Arts and briefly keeps them away.
It's not the first time something like this has happened, Bibeak. People try to get help from Rhodes Island without even reading the documentation.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: But this is not a good situation to be in. We risk angering them further if we stay.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: We should retreat before things get worse.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Are you afraid of failing a mission?
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: I... I don't know.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: It's my first field mission, and I don't want to give up like this.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: And we didn't do anything wrong!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I don't understand why they're driving us out after we helped them.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I used to hide behind my parents when I saw gloompincers. When someone hurt me, all I could think was 'what should I do?'
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: But I... I...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I don't want to leave like this, getting chased away like this!
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: The gloompincers edge forward, becoming less afraid of Orchid's Arts by the second.
Bibeak swings her sword.
She has done so to protect others from angry mobs before, and she has done so countless times in training.
But today, she has only herself in mind when she swings her sword.
Are you doing this because I'm Infected?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Does that make me worse than the gloompincers that are tearing your homes apart? Am I so scary that you have to hide away like that?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Even though we said we don't infect others with Oripathy?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: None of the villagers answer.
The swarm of gloompincers breaks through the barricade in front of the village.
Bibeak does not move her feet. She stands there holding her sword, raises it, swings it, and clenches her jaws.
(What a stubborn girl.)
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: (She's seeing the mission as a testament to her own worth. She didn't need to drive herself into a corner like that.)
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: (But if that's really how she's thinking of it...)
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: I'll help you out if you really want to do this, Bibeak.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: ...Just take it easy. You're hurt.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Damn it, the gloompincers are coming!
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Stand your ground! We'll stop them here!
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Grab your bows and farm tools!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Shut the windows and doors and make sure they're locked tight!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: More and more gloompincers rush towards the village, far more than originally expected.
At the same time, more and more villagers leave their houses and join the line.
The operators who've already begun preparing to evacuate look at Bibeak silently swinging her sword, sigh, and pick up their weapons again.
...Shit. Fine.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator B

attributes.content: Patty and I will go reinforce the barricades. This place is not where I want to die.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator B

attributes.content: I, I... stay away...
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: —My leg!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: If you're hurt, get out of the way.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: Stay away...! I, I can stand on my own...
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Oh, don't worry, I wouldn't dream of lending you a hand.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: The barricades are up! Over here, Orchid, Bibeak!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: Coming!
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: There's got to be an end to this!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Behind you!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: Thanks, bro! Er...
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Save it.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: Er, thanks...
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Don't just stand there, move your damn ass!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: You got anything better to do than stare? You say this village's so precious to you, but you're gonna leave a couple of Infected to fight for it?
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator B

attributes.content: Let me say this again: ordinary contact does not result in infection! Get your ass up here if you really want to chase away these gloompincers!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator B

attributes.content: Fine, dammit!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Take this! B-But just stay over there, I, I'll throw it over!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Suit yourself. Couldn't care less one way or another.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator B

attributes.content: I, I'm scared! But I-I do have a conscience!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: You saved my life! I've got to do the right thing!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: We made this odor bag! Gloompincers don't like the smell! It'll hold them off for a bit!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Catch!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Wright, look out for the other side...
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Aaaagh—
attributes.name: Frightened Voice

attributes.content: A scream draws everyone's attention. A little girl is pointing in Bibeak's direction with terror on her face.
A gloompincer raises its claw behind Bibeak. She tries to raise her sword, but fatigue gets the best of her.
A bolt pierces it just as it was about to bring its claws upon her.
The villager who fired the bolt shields her frightened daughter, and cocks her crossbow without a word as she turns her attention to another gloompincer.
Oh...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Are you okay, Bibeak? Pull back—
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: I'm fine, Orchid.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: T-They're coming!!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Cut the chatter! Get your ass to the barrier!
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: T-They're coming... I'm not scared!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Anyone who can still stand! Come and help them!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: Grab the improvised bombs! They'll at least do some damage!
attributes.name: Villager C

attributes.content: The sun begins to set, and the gloompincers finally back off, realizing that they are not making any headway.
The villagers continue to stand where they are, in a daze from the furious fighting, feeling only the soreness in their hands.
Bibeak uses her sword as a cane to support her own weight, before turning to head towards the Rhodes Island vehicle parked at a distance.
Bibeak! Get in, and I'll bandage your wounds.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Some of the villagers look as though they want to take a step forward, before stopping in their tracks.
...Hmph.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Field Operator A

attributes.content: I think we...
attributes.name: Villager A

attributes.content: Um, uh...
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: Sorry... and thank you. It's getting late. We can pack some food for you to eat on the way.
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: I mean it!
attributes.name: Villager B

attributes.content: No need. It's fine.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Orchid, I want some of those pastries you made.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: You brought some, didn't you?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Yeah, they're in the car.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Shall we go then?
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: There, all bandaged up.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: *Sobbing*...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: It was hard, wasn't it? Go ahead, you can cry.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: You were so brave. You didn't run back to the car crying; you came back on your own two feet after defeating the gloompincers.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: You changed the villagers' thinking and got them to fight alongside us.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: If it weren't for you, the rest of us would have turned around and left, venting about it the whole way back, and nothing would have changed.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Orchid...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I told myself countless times that I can't wallow in hate. I can't turn myself into something terrible.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: But that's what I look like in the eyes of the uninfected.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: But I... I don't think they're wrong.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: You don't have to console yourself like that, Bibeak.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Rhodes Island's documentation clearly stated that our squads contain Infected. It's their fault for not reading. The least they could have done was to handle it more politely, which we would have been able to accept.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: ...It's not consolation, Orchid, I really feel that way. It's only natural for them to be afraid, because... I'm afraid too. I hate and fear my condition.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I left home to come to Rhodes Island, in order to bring it under control. I participated in all that training to get this chance to conquer my fear...
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Maybe that's not something everyone can do.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: But I don't want to have done all that just to stop moving forward on my first field mission. Go backwards even.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Was I being selfish? If they were really scared, I shouldn't have—
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Lie down and have something to eat. Don't think too much about it.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: They were only afraid because they don't understand Oripathy. We've already explained that normal contact doesn't lead to infection.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: They calmed down and accepted that.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Will they ask for help from Rhodes Island again?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: If they do... will I be willing to accept the mission?
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: The choice is yours, Bibeak.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Everyone makes their own choices. If it were up to me... I'd probably turn it down after some thought.
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: ...I don't know what I'd think.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Maybe they won't be scared of us next time. Or maybe they'll reject us again. Or maybe there won't even be a next time.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: But I'll wait for that day.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: (Gives Bibeak some pastries)
attributes.name: Orchid

attributes.content: Thanks for being with me today, Orchid.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: Otherwise, I might have done something stupid.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: But I don't regret participating in this field mission, even if it was very different from what I imagined.
attributes.name: Bibeak

attributes.content: I'll keep moving forward.
attributes.name: Bibeak
